        "Every time a “$W$” is seen, the peak of the plausibility curve moves to the right, towards larger values of $p$. Every time an “$L$” is seen, it moves the other direction. The maximum height of the curve increases with each sample, meaning that fewer values of $p$ amass more plausibility as the amount of evidence increases. As each new observation is added, the curve is updated consistent with all previous observations.\n",
